data.title: USU Brand Toolkit | Area of Isolation Generator
data.meta_description: Utah State University's logos and trademarks are owned by the university, and they are valuable assets. Faculty, students, staff, and alumni share in the benefits associated with the logos and trademarks, and therefore also share responsibilities to ensure correct use. Utah State University Trademark Licensing office is to be consulted with any questions about university logos and their uses.
data.text: Files provided are not to be used on university stationary goods. The marks generated by the Area of Isolaiton generator are not available in the official logo library. Formal wordmarks and logos (marks) can only be created by University Marketing and Communications, Trademark Licensing. If you need access to a logo or folder that you do not currently have access to, contact trademark.licensing@usu.edu. New logo requests should be made via the logo request form in Service Now. Only college, administrative units (Vice President and above), statewide locations, and sub-brands will be issued official logo suites.
